entry.title: TabDragging tests: Set browser bounds using mouse emulation
entry.content:
On Linux ozone/wayland we can't control the browser bounds, but many

TabDragging tests expect specific bounds and will fail if the actual

bounds are different.



This CL introduces a workaround that allows us to still set the browser

bounds on this platform. The idea is to use ui_controls to emulate mouse

events that will resize and move the browser to where we want (like a

regular user would do).

entry.title: ServiceImageTransferCacheEntry: Prepare to separate out tone mapping
entry.content:
The function ServiceImageTransferCacheEntry::Deserialize is responsible

for both color conversion (which is arguably useless and shouldn't be

done) and tone mapping (which shouldn't be tied to image decode).



Prepare for decoupling tone mapping from image decode.



In ServiceImageTransferCacheEntry::Deserialize, save the state

that will be used for tone mapping.



Move tone mapping to the (for now private) function

ServiceImageTransferCacheEntry::GetImageWithToneMapApplied.



In ColorConversionSkFilterCache, remove the generic ConvertImage

function. Take the generic color conversion parts of the function

and inline them into ServiceImageTransferCacheEntry::Deserialize.

Rename the function to ApplyToneCurve.



In these functions, use the term "tone mapping" to refer to any

mechanism for adapting an image to a display of a specific HDR

headroom. Use the term "tone curve" to refer to a mapping that uses

a global curve (in contrast with local tone mapping performed by a

gainmap).

entry.title: Add support for suppressing custom cursors across all browser windows.
entry.content:
Custom cursors (in particular large custom images) set via CSS by a

web page can obscure elements in other browser windows if the

browser windows are positioned on top of each other. In those cases,

calling WebContents::CreateDisallowCustomCursorScope for the currently

focused WebContents is not sufficient to block custom cursors.



This CL adds a helper class to disallow custom cursor across all active

WebContents of all browser windows. Its current only use case is

Autofill popups, which is why the helper class is placed there. Should

it turn out to be needed elsewhere, it can still be moved.



One-pager (design discussions there, please):

go/disallow-custom-cursors-across-windows

entry.title: Change the calculation of
entry.content:
Prerender.Experimental.ReceivedPrerendersPerPrimaryPageChangedCount



This metric was introduced to investigate the overall usage amount of

speculation rules prerenders in one page. It was estimated by counting

the numbers of started_prerenders_ candidates on PrimaryPageChange.

Usage of started_prerenders_ was reasonable since its candidates are

reset per speculation rules removal, which reflects the developer's

intention.



However, after kPrerender2NewLimitAndScheduler is enabled, non-eager

prerender will be automatically canceled and eliminated from the

started_prerenders_ when reaching the limit. This means that it no

longer hold the prerenders that are expected to be counted when

recording the metric. Additionally, some reset mechanism not limited to

non-eager is planned to be introduced in the near future, so the same

problem could happen.



To solve this, this CL changes the calculation of received prerenders to

simply count up the received prerenders per

PrerendererImpl::MaybePrerender call, which will maintain the original

motivation of the metric and is expected to be consistent with future

changes. Also, this CL adds the "2" to the suffix of the histogram name.



OBSOLETE_HISTOGRAMS=Replaced with

ReceivedPrerendersPerPrimaryPageChangedCount2

entry.title: Pass top_frame_origin to URLLoader instead of WebURLRequestExtraData.
entry.content:
Currently a WebURLRequestExtraData is passed to URLLoader just for

passing the top frame origin to variations::VariationsURLLoaderThrottle

which sets `X-Client-Data` HTTP request header for Field Trials

Variations. RenderFrameImpl::WillSendRequestInternal() is setting the

top frame origin to the WebURLRequestExtraData.



This CL changes it to directly pass `top_frame_origin` to URLLoader. The

`top_frame_origin` can be retrieved from FetchContext by calling

GetTopFrameOrigin() method.



This CL introduces a behavior change of subresource fetching from

dedicated workers. Currently if a web worker on a Google domain would do

a fetch, it would be treated as non-first-party. But after this change,

the fetch will be treated as first-party.



Bug: 1379780

entry.title: Fix compile of C++ classes auto-generated from packed mojo structs.
entry.content:
Consider the following mojo struct:



```

struct Foo {

bool a@0;

[MinVersion=1] bool? b@1;

[MinVersion=2] bool? c@2;

}

```



Compilation will fail due to a duplicate constructor as the auto-generated C++ class looks like:



```

class Foo {

public:

Foo();

explicit Foo(bool a);

Foo(bool a, absl::optional b, absl::optional c);

Foo(bool a, absl::optional b, absl::optional c);

};

```



The duplicate constructor appears to be due to miscounting the number of

constructor parameters for some versions of the struct when there are

optional scalars present.



This CL attempts to fix counting of constructor parameters by using

the per version field count in the unpacked struct rather than the

packed struct which was previously cached in `version.num_fields`. Now, `version.num_fields` will contain unpacked field count while

`version.num_packed_fields` will contain packed field count.
